	[sam.trustRange 0 50
		|There’s a long pause after your question, during which a wide range of emotions war across the ausar’s scarred face. Finally she screws up her courage enough to say, <i>“No... No, I don’t want to go back. I want... to stay here with Briget [sam.hasKids
			|and my pup[sam.pupsRange 2
				|s
			]
		].”</i> Sam wasn’t looking directly at you while she was speaking, but when she finishes, she closes her eyes anyway and turns her body away from you with her arms crossed defensively.

		How do you respond to her defiance?
		|Sam hesitates, her fitful tail in her hands. <i>“O-ok [pc.name],”</i> she inhales, courage returning to the lean ausar woman, <i>“[sam.hasKids
			|I know my pup[sam.pupsRange 2
				|s
			] are in good hands with Briget, and the independence is good for their development!
			|I’ve stayed here with Briget long enough, and even if she is really kind to me...
		]”</i> She exhales, seemingly set in her decision to rejoin you. <i>“[sam.hasKids
			|Besides, you’ve
			|You’ve
		] been kind to me too. I think I’m ready to come back.”</i>
	]
	"])))

